 




<RINDOCK>[Declaration of Disaster Loan Area #2728; Amendment #1]</RINDOCK>



<DOCTITLE>Georgia; Declaration of Disaster Loan Area</DOCTITLE>


The above-numbered Declaration is hereby amended, in accordance with notices from the Federal Emergency Management
Agency dated July 14 and 19, 1994, to include Jasper, Newton, and Quitman Counties in the State of Georgia as a disaster
area as a result of damages caused by severe storms and flooding resulting from Tropical Storm Alberto on July 3, 1994,
and continuing.
In addition, applications for economic injury loans from small businesses located in the contiguous counties of
Morgan and Walton in the State of Georgia may be filed until the specified date at the previously designated location.
Any counties contiguous to the above-named primary counties and not listed herein have been previously declared.
All other information remains the same, i.e., the termination date for filing applications for physical damage is
September 4, 1994 and for economic injury the deadline is April 7, 1995.
The economic injury number for Georgia is 829300.



(Catalog of Federal Domestic Assistance Program Nos. 59002 and 59008.)



Dated: July 20, 1994.


<SIGNER>
Bernard Kulik,

